# wasm-pack output (regenerated by `pnpm run build:wasm` -> scripts/build-wasm.sh).
# Two builds: the portable single-threaded one, and the multi-threaded one (rayon over a Web Worker
# pool). Both are generated, so neither is committed — the release workflow builds them at publish
# time (prepublishOnly), which is how the .wasm binaries reach the npm tarball. Nothing else needs a
# Rust toolchain: the website installs the published package rather than compiling the engine.
wasm/
wasm-mt/
# tsc output (regenerated by `pnpm run build:ts`)
dist/
node_modules/
